Black Friday is upon us, and there are many great deals available from South Africa’s leading stores. Game and Makro have both announced that they will be offering 4 weeks of Black Friday deals rather than the usual, limited sale period. Takealot will be offering three weeks of “Blue Dot Countdown” deals in the build-up to the big day. These countdown deals will include the following: However, there are sometimes products that you cannot buy locally and therefore may require you to shop from overseas stores instead. Additionally, sometimes these stores are simply more affordable – even when you account for shipping costs and import taxes. We have listed some of the most popular overseas online stores that you can buy from as a South African. Amazon is undoubtedly the world’s most well known online store and offers an incredible array of products. Not all Amazon products can be purchased from South Africa, however, and this will be made evident when you try to place these products into your cart. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-273511" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Amazon-smartphone.jpg" alt="Amazon smartphone" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Amazon-smartphone.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Amazon-smartphone-300x202.jpg 300w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Amazon-smartphone-595x400.jpg 595w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> eBay continues to be one of the largest ecommerce websites in the world. It is a great place to find a variety of great deals, and it also provides an estimated Rand price when you are searching through its catalogue. Much like Amazon, eBay stocks products across just about every category, and is worth considering as an alternative to the aforementioned ecommerce giant. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-268863" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/ebay-office-logo.jpg" alt="ebay office logo" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/ebay-office-logo.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/ebay-office-logo-300x202.jpg 300w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/ebay-office-logo-595x400.jpg 595w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> Gearbest is a Chinese retailer that is predominantly, but not exclusively, focused on technology and electronics. As a strategic branch of Chinese cross-border enterprise Globalegrow, it is a great place to buy Chinese branded products including Xiaomi smartphones. However, there are many products not made by Chinese companies, too. You can set your store to deliver to South Africa and show products in Rand, and shipping is easy to view on each product’s dedicated page. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-256505" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Gearbest-headline-image.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Gearbest-headline-image.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Gearbest-headline-image-300x202.jpg 300w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Gearbest-headline-image-595x400.jpg 595w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> Steam is the global hub for PC games and has an incredibly large range of video games to choose from. You will not need to worry about shipping as all purchases are in the form of electronic access through the Steam platform. While it is primarily known as a gaming platform, Steam also offers a range of other digital products including game development, audio, animation, and video software. AliExpress is an iteration of Chinese ecommerce giant Alibaba that specifically focuses on selling products to a global audience. AliExpress offers South African shipping and prices, and covers an extensive number of product ranges – making it a great place to browse. The platform also offers buyer protection, making it a safe option when it comes to international shopping. <img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-373022" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/aliexpress-640x430.jpg" alt="aliexpress" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/aliexpress-640x430.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/aliexpress-596x400.jpg 596w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/aliexpress-300x202.jpg 300w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/aliexpress.jpg 670w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> Banggood is another Chinese ecommerce company that has become a popular option for South Africans looking to get cheap deals. It offers an extensive range of products including electronics, smartphones, clothing, and remote-controlled toys. On its home page, it offers flash deals which can hold offer discounts in excess of 50%. <img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-373147" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/Banggood-640x430.jpg" alt="Banggood" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/Banggood.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/Banggood-595x400.jpg 595w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/Banggood-300x202.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" />